subSubSection.paragraph:
MATERIAL EXAMINED. —
New Caledonia .
LAGON , stn 0129, 22°30.5’S , 166°47.2’E , 45 m , 23.VIII.1984 , 1 damaged colony with 4 stems on barnacle shell, no gonothecae ( MNHN ).

Philippines .
MUSORSTOM 3, stn DR 117, 12°31.2’N , 120°39.3’E , 92-97 m ,
3. VI .1985
, 1 colony with 8 stems without gonothecae ( MNHN ).

Norfolk Ridge. SMIB 4, stn DW 50, 23°42.4’- 23°41.6’S , 168°00.8’- 168°00.6’E , 260-295 m , 9.III.1989 , c. 10- 15 mm high stems on worm-tubes, no gonothecae ( MNHN ).— Stn DW 55, 23°21.4’- 23°21.4’S , 168°04.5’- 168°04.8’E , 215-260 m , 9.III.1989 , 1 colony on Bryozoa with immature gonothecae ( MNHN ).

SMIB 5, stn DW 95, 22°59.7’S , 168°19.8’E , 200 m , 14.IX.1989 , 1 stem with gonothecae on basal part of
Monostaechas quadridens ( McCrady, 1859 ) (MNHN)
. — Stn DW 101, 23°21.2’S , 168°04.9’E , 270 m , 14.IX.1989 , 1 small colony growing on stem of
M. quadridens
, no gonothecae ( MNHN ).

Our specimens were collected from New Caledonia , the Philippines and the Norfolk Ridge. The depth range at those localities was between 45 and
295 m .
